cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with the complexity of algorithms and lower bounds, which suggests it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of an advice tape oracle and the focus on online algorithms suggest it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the combinatorial nature of the presented algorithm suggests it could belong to cs.GT (Discrete Mathematics).
